entries.name: BridgeHub
entries.description: Sits between the shared bridge and the StateTransitionManager(s) and relays L1 <-> L2 messages from the shared bridge or other ZK stack chains to their respective destinations.

issuedPermissions.description: register new tokens in the BridgeHub and create new chains sharing the Elastic Chain contracts.

chainsCreated.description: All new chains created go thorugh the central bridgehub and are thus stored here with their respective STMs.

receivedPermissions.description: register new tokens in the BridgeHub and create new chains sharing the Elastic Chain contracts.
manage the shared ValidatorTimelock contract address, revert batches and set permissioned validators for all chains connected to the StateTransitionManager.
register new Elastic Chains in the shared bridge.

entries.name: Guardians
entries.description: Custom Multisig implementation that has a general threshold of 5 and a specific threshold for extending the legal voting period of 2.

receivedPermissions.description: extend the legal veto period, approve a protocol upgrade.

entries.name: SecurityCouncil
entries.description: Custom Multisig implementation that has a general threshold of 9 but also specific thresholds for upgrade approvals (6) or soft freezes (3).

receivedPermissions.description: soft freeze, hard freeze, approve a protocol upgrade.

softFreezeNonce.description: Increments with each softFreeze (freezes ALL Hyperchains (blocks Mailbox and Executor facets) connected to the main STM for SOFT_FREEZE_PERIOD

hardFreezeNonce.description: Increments with each hardFreeze (freezes ALL Hyperchains (blocks Mailbox and Executor facets) connected to the main STM for HARD_FREEZE_PERIOD

references.text: Security Council members - ZK Nation docs

entries.name: StateTransitionManager
entries.description: Defines L2 diamond contract creation and upgrade data, the proof system for the `ZKsync diamond` contract connected to it (and other L2 diamond contracts that share the logic).

issuedPermissions.description: manage the shared ValidatorTimelock contract address, revert batches and set permissioned validators for all chains connected to the StateTransitionManager.

entries.name: L1SharedBridge
entries.description: This bridge contract escrows all ERC-20s and ETH that are deposited to registered ZK stack chains like ZKsync Era.

issuedPermissions.description: register new Elastic Chains in the shared bridge.

entries.name: ProtocolUpgradeHandler
entries.description: The central upgrade contract and Governance proxy for all ZK stack contracts. Accepts successful DAO proposals from L2, emergency proposals from the EmergencyUpgradeBoard. The three members of the EmergencyUpgradeBoard also have special roles and permissions in this contract.

issuedPermissions.description: extend the legal veto period, approve a protocol upgrade.
soft freeze, hard freeze, approve a protocol upgrade.

protocolFrozenUntil.description: Timestamp until which ALL Hyperchains connected to the main STM are frozen. (Mailbox and Executor facets blocked)
